From e473b179309068f834e58e9e8d7fd128718779f5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <fix@anthropic.com>
Date: Fri, 1 May 2026 10:58:45 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] GPU-batched env + parallel launcher

environment.py:
  - Runs ENV_BATCH=128 parallel channel realizations per step using torch
  - MMSE beamformer computed as batched torch.linalg.inv on GPU
  - H_eff, G, SINR all computed in one fused GPU kernel per step
  - V100 now sees 128x larger matmul ops -> proper GPU utilization

train_drl.py:
  - Uses batched env: each step produces ENV_BATCH=128 transitions
  - 4 gradient updates per env step to keep GPU busy
  - Effective throughput: 128 * 1000 steps * 200 eps = 25.6M transitions
  - select_action_batch() added to DDPG for batch actor inference

run_drl_parallel.sh:
  - Trains N=4,8,16,32,64 simultaneously on GPUs 3,4,5,6,7
  - Logs to logs/drl_N{N}.log
  - --quick flag for fast sanity check (200 eps x 500 steps)

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
